text:
A week after the current Blackhawks players received their Stanley Cup rings, former Blackhawks Patrick Sharp and Johnny Oduya received their rings in Dallas.
The Blackhawks' massive Stanley Cup rings are here Sharp and Oduya, now both members of the Stars, were presented with their rings by Blackhawks VP of Hockey Ops Al MacIsaac, and the team tweeted out a picture of the mini ceremony.
New bling alert!
VP of Hockey Ops Al MacIsaac presented Oduya and @10PSharp with championship rings in Dallas. pic.twitter.com/e7kTHycJ4M
— Chicago Blackhawks (@NHLBlackhawks) October 13, 2015
